<heading box="[718,869,1060,1086]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
(
<figureCitation box="[726,860,1060,1086]" captionStart="Figs 24–27" captionStartId="13.[317,360,1780,1801]" captionTargetBox="[320,1267,609,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-71@13.[317,1269,605,1750]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24–27. Pilobatella brevipila sp. n.: 24 = body in dorsal view, 25 = body in ventral view, 26 = genital plate, 27 = lamella and sensillus" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731996" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731996/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs 24–27</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[317,1270,1131,1297]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis: Body surface smooth. Rostral apex widely rounded. Lamellae short, converging, continuing laterally in a short, weakly developed anterolateral crest. Lamellar cusps bearing very short lamellar setae, interlamellar setae also very short. Sensillus long, well barbed. Notogaster with ten pairs of very short setae and four pairs of small, round sacculi. All legs monodactylous.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[317,1271,1332,1382]" box="[382,1271,1332,1353]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<materialsCitation box="[382,1271,1332,1353]" collectingDate="2008-04-17" country="Madagascar" location="Vohimana reserve" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
